scanByPrefix

public static <T> List<Map.Entry<String,T>> scanByPrefix(Persistence<T> persistence,
                                                         String prefix,
                                                         int max)
Finds zero or more entries that start with a given prefix

Parameters:
prefix - a string that all keys found should start with.
max - a maximum amount of elements to return. The implementation of the store may choose to return less (for example, if a store can only fetch 10 elements per query, then setting a max of 1000 will still only return 10), but never more.
Returns:
a list of up to max key/value pairs, ordered by key

Finds zero or more entries that are within a given range, with the start also being exclusive.

Parameters:
start - a lower bound of the range of keys to look in (exclusive)
end - an upper bound of the range of keys to look in (exclusive)
max - a maximum amount of elements to return. The implementation of the store may choose to return less (for example, if a store can only fetch 10 elements per query, then setting a max of 1000 will still only return 10), but never more.
Returns:
a list of up to max key/value pairs, ordered by key

Finds zero or more entries that start with a given prefix. Uses a reverse scan.

Parameters:
prefix - a string that all keys found should start with.
max - a maximum amount of elements to return. The implementation of the store may choose to return less (for example, if a store can only fetch 10 elements per query, then setting a max of 1000 will still only return 10), but never more.
Returns:
a list of up to max key/value pairs, ordered by key (descending)
